19
20 SECTION 13. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
21 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. USES OF
22 FUNDS. The funds appropriated in this Act shall be used to defray the
23 necessary expenses of the operation of the Office of the Speaker of the House
24 of Representatives, the Office of the Chief of Staff, the Office of the
25 Coordinator of House Legislative Services, the Office of Parliamentarian, the
26 Chief Clerk's Office, House Member Services Office and other reasonable and
27 necessary expenses of the House of Representatives of the General Assembly
28 incurred during the fiscal year ending June 30, 2025 2026. Any balance
29 remaining on June 30, 2024 2025 in the funds provided by this Act shall be
30 made available for the fiscal year ending June 30, 2025 2026 and for the same
31 purposes.
32
33 SECTION 14. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
34 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. TRANSFER
35 AUTHORITY. If the Speaker of the House and the Chief of Staff or his
36 designee determine that any item or portion thereof appropriation herein for
6 04-03-2025 11:44:10 JAR006

As Engrossed: H4/3/25 HB1003
1 a specific purpose is not needed for such purpose, they may certify such fact
2 to the State Auditor and the State Auditor shall cause a transfer to be made
3 from one item to another between any appropriations authorized by the General
4 Assembly for the House of Representatives.
5
6 SECTION 15. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
7 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. SALARIES.
8 In order that exceptionally well-qualified personnel may be recruited and
9 retained, the House of Representatives may exceed the maximum salary levels
10 by no more than twenty percent (20%) for no more than one-third (1/3) of the
11 positions authorized in their operation appropriation act, may exceed the
12 maximum salary levels for the purpose of merit adjustments for all positions,
13 and may promote a maximum of two grades for no more than one-third (1/3) of
14 the classified positions authorized in its operation appropriation act.
15
16 SECTION 16. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
17 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
18 AUDIO/VISUAL POLICY. The appropriations provided herein to produce audio or
19 video materials by or under the direction of the House of Representatives
20 shall not be used for the following:
21 (a) A person may not use audio or video materials produced by or under the
22 direction of the House of Representatives in political or campaign
23 advertising.
24 (b) A person may not use audio or video materials produced by or under
25 the direction of the House of Representatives for a commercial purpose.
26 (1) In this section, "commercial purpose" means a purpose that
27 is intended to result in a profit or other tangible benefit.
28 (c) The House Management Committee may give permission to an entity to
29 use the audio or video materials for public education governmental
30 broadcast which shall not conflict with subsection (b).
31
32 SECTION 17. COMPLIANCE WITH OTHER LAWS. Disbursement of funds
33 authorized by this act shall be limited to the appropriation for such agency
34 and funds made available by law for the support of such appropriations; and
35 the restrictions of the State Procurement Law, the General Accounting and
36 Budgetary Procedures Law, the Revenue Stabilization Law, the Regular Salary
7 04-03-2025 11:44:10 JAR006

As Engrossed: H4/3/25 HB1003
1 Procedures and Restrictions Act, or their successors, and other fiscal
2 control laws of this State, where applicable, and regulations promulgated by
3 the Department of Finance and Administration, as authorized by law, shall be
4 strictly complied with in disbursement of said funds.
5
6 SECTION 18. LEGISLATIVE INTENT. It is the intent of the General
7 Assembly that any funds disbursed under the authority of the appropriations
8 contained in this act shall be in compliance with the stated reasons for
9 which this act was adopted, as evidenced by the Agency Requests, Executive
10 Recommendations and Legislative Recommendations contained in the budget
11 manuals prepared by the Department of Finance and Administration, letters, or
12 summarized oral testimony in the official minutes of the Arkansas Legislative
13 Council or Joint Budget Committee which relate to its passage and adoption.
14
15 SECTION 19. EMERGENCY CLAUSE. It is found and determined by the
16 General Assembly, that the Constitution of the State of Arkansas prohibits
17 the appropriation of funds for more than a one (1) year period; that the
18 effectiveness of this Act on July 1, 2025 is essential to the operation of
19 the agency for which the appropriations in this Act are provided, and that in
20 the event of an extension of the legislative session, the delay in the
21 effective date of this Act beyond July 1, 2025 could work irreparable harm
22 upon the proper administration and provision of essential governmental
23 programs. Therefore, an emergency is hereby declared to exist and this Act
24 being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public peace, health
25 and safety shall be in full force and effect from and after July 1, 2025.
26
